### 4. 🤖 Doola
**URL**: `doola.com`  
**Price**: $297/yr (Starter) → $1,999/yr (Tax & Compliance) → $2,999/yr (Business-in-a-Box)

#### ✅ What's Great
| Element | Details |
|---|---|
| **"For Do'ers" branding** | Catchy, action-oriented identity that appeals to SaaS/ecom founders |
| **AI Co-Founder feature** | Unique differentiator — AI assistant for business decisions |
| **Progressive pricing tiers** | Clear Starter → Pulse → Tax & Compliance → Business-in-a-Box ladder |
| **Feature comparison table** | Full matrix with checkmarks across all 4 tiers |
| **VIP Club upsell** | $1000+ exclusive perks layer — smart premium positioning |
| **Bookkeeping/tax included** | Higher tiers include dedicated bookkeeper + IRS filings — true full-service |
| **Modern UI/UX** | Clean, well-spaced, toggle between Annual/Monthly pricing |

#### ❌ What's Wrong
| Issue | Impact |
|---|---|
| **No residential address offering** | Only "mailing address" — no lease docs, no utility bills, no bank-compliance focus |
| **$297 starter looks cheap but is bare** | Formation + RA only — EIN, banking, all extras are upsells |
| **No ITIN service** | Missing a critical need for non-US founders |
| **Price creep to $2,999** | Full stack is 12× your total cost — massive price gap |
| **Overwhelm factor** | Too many tiers + add-ons + toggles — analysis paralysis risk |
| **US-focused marketing** | Doesn't strongly target India/UAE/Malaysia/France specifically |
| **No speed promise** | No "same-day" or "24h" delivery claims |

